'''QuikWiki''' QuikReference Page.

        * Return to the HomePage.

  The URL for the HomePage is: 
    '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi/?HomePage'''  

  A shortcut is: 
    '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi/?'''

  Or even more briefly: 
    '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki'''
  if the Web server and QuikWiki configuration permit this.

        * View a page named ''MyPage,'' or create it if it doesn't exist.

  '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi/?MyPage'''


        * Edit ''MyPage.''

   '''http//''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi/?MyPage&action=edit'''


        * Click on the '''Edit''' link above to view the markup tags on this page.  The text markup is similar to WikiWiki, and provides formatting that includes ''emphasized (italic),'' '''bold,''',

   preformatted text,

        * Lists,

and horizontal rules.
----

Alternatively, enter the complete URL of the '''edit''' link above: 

   '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi?QuikReference&action=edit'''.

        * JPEG and GIF images are displayed in-line in pages, or separately using the '''image''' word.

        * The '''words''' word lists all of the wiki words.  Enter:

   '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi?words'''

        * Page templates can contain embedded Perl scripts.  The files, '''WikiHeader,'''
'''WikiFooter,''' and '''eg/ODBCTable.cgi''' (in the source archive) are examples.

        * Click on the '''doc''' link above to view the manual.  The link uses the '''doc''' word:

   '''http://''server_name''/quikwiki/quikwiki.cgi?doc'''
